post_text: Thank you for your valor, Canaan!
shared_text:
Do√±a Ana County Government Center added a new photo to the album: Community Involvement.
April 14 at 2:12 PM ¬∑

The Do√±a Ana Board of County Commissioners has declared April 14, 2020 as CANAAN BOWER DAY OF VALOR!

Canaan (pictured middle with his parents) thwarted an attempted kidnapping in progress on March 25 by pinning the suspect to the ground until a Do√±a Ana County Sheriff's Department Deputy arrived on the scene.

His act of courage, bravery and heroism has been recognized nationally and our community is stronger for having Canaan in it.

We honor Canaan and his family with this well-deserved proclamation and invite everyone in Do√±a Ana County to celebrate him today by liking, sharing or commenting on this post. Way to go, Canaan!

#TeenageHero #CommunityInvolvement #Proclamation
Mayfield High School

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

As you are now aware, schools in New Mexico will remained closed for the rest of the school year in order contain the COVID-19 pandemic. The state has also mandated that school districts and charter schools develop and implement a ‚ÄúContinuous Learning Plan‚Äù to enable students demonstrate competency and meet graduation requirements. Alma‚Äôs staff will be meeting on Monday to discuss the state‚Äôs mandate and create a Continuous Learning Plan that meets the needs of our learning community. Please continue to visit our website and Facebook page for updated information.

Stay well by continuing to stay home as much as possible, practice social/physical distancing when it is necessary for you to leave your home and washing your hands regularly.

Alma‚Äôs staff will be meeting on Monday to discuss the state‚Äôs mandate and create a Continuous Learning Plan that meets the needs of our learning community. Please continue to visit our website and Facebook page for updated information.

Stay well by continuing to stay home as much as possible, practice social/physical distancing when it is necessary for you to leave your home and washing your hands regularly.

As you already know, the State has closed schools starting next week with a reopening set for April 6. There is school tomorrow. It is important that students attend tomorrow so that we can disseminate more specific information about how Alma will continue to meet the educational needs of students.

Remember to wash your hands regularly and cover your coughs and sneezes. If you feel unwell, seek medical attention immediately. If you have travelled out of the State since February 27, call the following NM Department of Health hotline: 855-600-3453.

Public Charter Schools of New Mexico
May 29, 2019 at 12:20 PM ¬∑

The US House of Representatives is cutting $40 million in funding to the Charter School Program. We can let our Senators know that this cut is unacceptable for the thousands of students and their families who attend or are waiting to attend charter schools. post_text: From Irene: The Arts and Cultural District is going to have a booth Today! Also, they are doing a Giving Day and any money raised by the non-profit will be matched dollar for dollar by the Community Foundation and Untied Way. Children and youth from 1st grade to 18 years will be given two chips that are worth $5 each for them to contribute to any group they want. They will also be given a Caliche gift certificate that is worth an ice cream when they visit three to five groups. People can sign up to volunteer to the groups as well. At our booth people can choose to volunteer for the Zombie Walk (Alma already participates in the dance); Salsa Fest, the Chile Drop, or different Arts and Cultural District events. Should be a great time!

post_text: Good easy cookies! Anyone raised on these cookies? Happy Sunday!
shared_text:
Marsha Marsh‚ÄéAppalachian Foods and Recipes
October 19, 2015 at 8:17 PM ¬∑

Old Fashioned Vanilla Tea Cakes

Mix 3 cups self-rising flour & 2 cups sugar.
Add in: 2 sticks softened butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 4 Tablespoons milk, and 2 eggs. I don‚Äôt cut out the cookies, just drop from a spoon.

Generously space apart on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam as they do spread. Bake 350 degree oven for 8 - 10 minutes or until done as you want them.
text:

Marsha Marsh‚ÄéAppalachian Foods and Recipes
October 19, 2015 at 8:17 PM ¬∑

Old Fashioned Vanilla Tea Cakes

Mix 3 cups self-rising flour & 2 cups sugar.
Add in: 2 sticks softened butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 4 Tablespoons milk, and 2 eggs. I don‚Äôt cut out the cookies, just drop from a spoon.

Generously space apart on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam as they do spread. Bake 350 degree oven for 8 - 10 minutes or until done as you want them.
